13.9. PDF: Distributions

These merges will be available from the Distribution screen.

  


Award Review Form

The Award Review form will have the following edits, as demonstrated by [[File:Award Review Form.pdf]]:

  * The "four areas" should become "three areas".
  * Item #1 should read, "Total tuition and fees owed by the family, less any scholarships received from another organization."
  * Item #2 should be removed.
  * Item #3 should read, "Students enrolled"
  * Item #4 should read, "Student grade levels, LD (Learning Disability) status, & OSDC qualifications (if applicable)"
  * The "Other Aid" and corresponding "Correction" column should be removed.



  


The "Total Tuition Awards" amount will include the application fee totals.

  


The "Other Aid" column was in the original system but will NOT be in the new system. The Total Tuition amount will be called "Family Tuition" instead.

  


This report will be sent by email. The email should look like this:

  


Subject: School award review form

 

Dear <school contact first name>,

 

Attached is the report showing proposed scholarship awards for <school name>. Please review this proposal and let us know of any changes you would like to make. Once we receive a signed copy of the attached proposal, we will process the awards for your school.

 

Sincerely,

 

Vivian Mast

Scholarship Services Coordinator

 

Faith Builders Scholarship Services

    An ECFA Accredited Organization

28527 Guys Mills Road

Guys Mills, PA 16327

 

(814) 789-4518 ext. 0

Fax: (814) 789-3396

  


The wording can be copied from [[File:Award Review Form.rtf]], and the design can be modeled after the PDF.

  


Award Letters

The Award Letters are the same for a September and November school. Unlike the report in the prior database, we will not display the 70%/30% split since FB will send a full payment up-front.

All families $0 award should be excluded

  


See [[File:Award Letter.rtf]] for reference.

  


Award Notification

This is sent to the parents. It should show a list of students with the total amount awarded. However, the tuition should not be broken down on a per-child basis.

All families $0 award should be excluded

  


For example: [[File:Award Notification.rtf]] 

  


Family Envelopes

This will be envelopes for all families who were awarded tuition.

All families $0 award should be excluded

  


Postcards

The postcards will be printed based on the information specified for the Business. For example:

  


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

  


Note that we do NOT need to import the business cards.

  


These postcards can be printed from the school screen. We should generate a PDF with postcards for all contributing businesses, and FB can choose how many to print.

  


These postcards are connected to the year that the contributions were designated to the school (if the school's year on the contribution matches the school year of the distribution). If the school chooses to defer some of the funds, the postcards will not be printed the following year.

  


Envelopes

This is an envelope with the school address. It can be called "School Envelope".

  


The standard signature name and title can be set in AppHosting.zone settings.
